      },
      "date": "2012-04-19 21:11:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe trivial patch looks like it does what is intended, but whenever I see something like this I ask whether there was a reason that this function has been removed?\n\nWhat was the original reason for adding this code?  Has the BKL or other requirement been removed from newer kernels, or at least from the unmount path?  There was some work done in BKL removal.  It is worth a few minutes to investigate the reasoning and add a useful comment for the future if it is still needed, or possibly drop this complexity entirely for new kernels rather than just keep an unnecessary workaround in place forever.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
